Lee Chin wrote:
> 
> Does this mean to say that If I link my application with glibc, I have to
> gove away my code under either GPL or a more liberal licence?
> 
IIRC, glibc is licensed under the L-GPL, which lets you link it without
mandating a GPL license on your software. If glibc had been licensed
under the GPL, that would be the case.
Last I remember seeing though, RMS was trying to convince people not to
use the LGPL.
